<%= render "header" %>

<%= react_component("DeferredRenderApp", props: {}, prerender: true) %>
<hr/>

<h2>Deferred Rendering of Async Routes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      Use register to expose the rendering function to ReactOnRails on the client side:
    </p>
    <pre>
  import DeferredRenderApp from './DeferredRenderAppRenderer';

  ReactOnRails.registerRenderer({
    DeferredRenderApp,
  });
    </pre>
    <h4>spec/dummy/client/app/startup/clientRegistration.jsx</h4>
    <br>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>Don't register rendering functions on the server side. Instead, create a generator function for use on the server:</p>
    <pre>
  import DeferredRenderApp from './DeferredRenderAppServer';

  ReactOnRails.register({
    DeferredRenderApp,
  });
    </pre>
    <h4>spec/dummy/client/app/startup/serverRegistration.jsx</h4>
    <br>
  </li>

  <li>
    See <b>spec/dummy/client/app/startup/DeferredRenderAppRenderer.jsx</b> and <b>spec/dummy/client/app/startup/DeferredRenderAppServer.jsx</b>
  </li>
</ul>
